@node "Install" "Installation of the heuristik scanner module"
@{b}How to install the heuristik module ?@{ub}

In the now spread VirusWorkshop versions (5.x), the heuristik scanner will be
a part of the mainprogramm. To ensure a better update possibility only for
this module, I will implent a alone standing binary block, which has to be
copied in the actual programmdirectory or in the "VW:" assign.

As said, this is just future.
@endnode

@node "Introduction" "What is it for a new option/module ?"

 This is just an additional tool for freaky users. It offers you the
 possibility to search for dangerous structures and stuff like that. It can
 cause a lot of FALSE positives, but it`s (as said) a tool for the more
 advanced users.
@endnode

@node "Heuristics" "What does heuristic exactly mean ?"

 Heuristic is a word, which is nowadays on the PC very popular and every
 better viruskiller offers you this possibility. Due to my contacts to some
 PC antivirus people and to the Virus Test Center in Hamburg, I came to the
 conclusion to implent such a scanner on AMIGA. Heuristic scanners search for
 dangerous filestructures and commands and give the user a warning. Such
 filestructures can e.g. appear in a lot of software

 e.g. all packers look for special hunkstructures (ProPack etc.)

 a lot of non crypted antivirus software can contain such commands
@endnode

